The D-block is in a rural area which includes three small villages;
{Penton Grafton} {Fyfield} {Appleshaw}
The main road from{Andover}to {Ludgershall,}the{A342,}runs South-East to North-West almost making a diagonal across the block. Beside it is a branch{railway line}used by the Ministry of Defence for freight.
Small country{lanes}form a network across the block with a subsidiary pattern of{footpaths}and bridleways. The original{Domesday Survey}mentions all three of the villages and much of the character in existence in 1086 is still in evidence to this day.
